{
  "stem": "24212.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if anything, don't forget that Czechoslovakia was under communists, and barely anything came out unless they wanted it to come out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they would enlarge or embellish certain aspects which had nothing to do with the Western allies for instance, only the Russians.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And even that-- I don't read Russian.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, I could read one sentence in-- in five minutes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I won't bother with that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So very little is today known about the eastern part of the resistance.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I should have prepared a map.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, you know Czechoslovak is like a sausage-- long country with a head.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm just thinking for one second if I have very handily a map.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No-- I-- Should I draw you a map, or it's not necessary?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well anyhow, the tail end is Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So it's narrowing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And on top you have Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, where they came from in Poland, I have no idea.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then-- so evidently there must have been some Poles involved, when they got out for instance, the Pierres-- the Frenchmen-- when they got away from the-- from the prisoner of war camp.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And somebody got them through the border, which must have been very difficult, because it's highly mountainous, you know, like the Rockies, the Tatra Mountains.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then they must have gotten to Presov or nearby.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then somebody brought them across the border into Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And from the Slovak border, they took them to where we picked them up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We took them on the Slovak-Hungarian border.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In Hungary, somebody else picked them-- it's like a chain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And you usually knew one person to contact, you know, or that person contacted you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I'm sending you two packages.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "One is a little bit torn, which means he limps, or he's sick or something.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
